In this article, President Biden discusses various topics during a press conference. He mentions that the banking crisis is under control, but they are still considering whether further legislation is needed. When asked about the Nashville school shooting, the President says he has no idea if Christians were targeted and jokes that if Senator Josh Hawley believes they were, then he probably doesn't. On the topic of Israel's democracy, Biden says he doesn't think they are at an inflection point but acknowledges that they are in a difficult spot and need to work it out. When asked about Russia sending tactical nuclear weapons to Belarus, the President expresses concern and calls it dangerous talk from Putin.